content: Frequently crashes on Chrome OS 88 when opening folders.
Pretty good but old interface. Please update with modern UI.
Excellent app, most useful app I have. I have lots on webdav servers and this enables several users to have access from anywhere . My customers love it. Highly recommend it.
great app
Tried to upload a large amount of pictures, but stopped halfway uploading.
Latest update broke app. Tried clearing data and reinstall. App force closes at startup
When I click on the PDF I see a blank page when it downloads.  Help!
Crashes immediatly after start on Android N. Refunding.

Would be better if I could schedule the sync. That being said, this is the ONLY app that actually adheres to webdav standard (I can tell because integrated webdav solutions in php like nextcloud don't play well with nonstandard) so its the only webdav client that can do synchronization without breaking on the play store right now. Its simple, easy and to the point. Just wish I could schedule syncs'
Works exactly how a webdav client should! Thank you for making this. It makes file management on put.io SO much easier.
But it would be nice to have automatic file syncing. Seems silly to have to manually sync changes.
Best Webdav app there is.  Works perfectly with owncloud!

Worth $3 for sure, works with my owncloud instance better than the sadly neglected official client. Tons of features, well designed, even slick.  A few gripes/suggestions: 1. Scheduled or active synching would be appreciated 2. Background synching please!!! 3. I really do wish it was FOSS 4. When I click synched photos/slideshows on my remote drive... I wish it was smart enough to use the local file. 5. Setting up accounts via account manager would make more sense ultimately.

Should give this app 4 stars because it could use some minor improvements in certain areas but it works very well and is the only webdav client that has android and ios versions.  Thanks for adding the file tree fallback.  Works perfectly with my ownCloud server.
Best app out there to access your WebDAV server for both iOS and Android. Quick setup and solid syncing. Please keep up the great work!

This tool has become a key component very quickly to my sharing and syncing solution for all my files. I'm able to connect to my OwnCloud instance and sync all my music and photos down to my external SD card. Even though there was a bug in the local path to sync down to I was able to receive a fix for it the same day which I can't tell you how much I appreciate it. This is far and away worth the money.
The dev responded to my question (I made a mistake entering the server info) with the fix very quickly!!!!  Been using this for years & it works great, does just what it says!

Nice app for syncing but a couple suggestions.  When performing a sync, preserve the file info (created/modified date.) Also, maybe a keep-alive option in settings so phone won't sleep while performing a sync.  Other than that, loving it.
Great app. Totally worth the money. It would be awesome to be able to download folders that have nested folders in them.
Only webdav app I've found to log onto my noontec n5. But it closes down unexpectedly too often, and my media player can't see through it to the n5. So work still needed.
Work perfect very functional & stable
Can't seem to reach my https server on a nonstandard port, no good.

This is the best, most feature-complete webdav client. It supports every type of authentication I needed. It is also the same app/ui for Android and iOS, which is important in heterogeneous environments.  The best part, though, is the developer himself. He is incredibly helpful and responsive. I needed support for NTLM ("Windows") authentication, which does not come "for free" in Android, as it does in iOS, and Sean added that in his next release, within a day! That is very impressive.
Best webdav app so far.  Could really use a sync feature, would give it 5 stars for sure.
The best WebDAV app I have found and the dev was incredibly quick to respond to a feature request.
The *best* WebDAV client there is for Android! Works flawlessly.
An excellent WebDAV client.
I have self signed webdav server on qnap, and only this program seems to work with it.
Exactly what is needed!
Desperately needs folder upload support and select all option when browsing for files to upload.
Works nice and smooth which us great. could hopefully be improved with folder sync for back up/synchro purposes. please keep going and develop it more
Best webdav out there, thanks.
Nice Please enable move to SD card. Works perfectly with memopal. Add upload folder and scheduled uploads and it would be perfect.
Does exactly what it says on the tin

I already had the iphone version of this and it worked flawlessly. I bought the Android version for my Sony P Tablet. There was an issue with it crashing so I e-mailed tech support. Within a few hours I had a reply and by 10 AM this morning less than 12 hours later an updated version had been released. This new version works perfectly and I am using it to connect to Mydisk and Apples iDisk.   This is excedllent tech support service, please take a note Apple and Microsoft how it should be done.
This is an excellent application for WHS. I bought it for my iphone a year ago and i bought it again for my new galaxy s2 Thanks
Fantastic app. Using it to access my owncloud server. Works perfectly.
Do all the tricks
Excellent app, superb support
Nice
Well maintained and a lot better than cloud solutions.
works okay in general. cannot delete a folder that I just created. Doesn't seem to flush file or folder changes to server. Doesn't work well w/ unico
Good app unfortunately missing complete folder upload, only single files.
5th stars if you can move files to other Webdav folders on the same server. In addition the download of large files fail quite frequently :(
The toolbar with the small unlabeled icons is very clumsy to use. Maybe just use labeled buttons for common actions and a popup menu for the rest?
Authentication to my Windows Server 2003 with IIS doesn't work. Requires plain text password sending to work so SSL is mandatory in my opinion.
FC as soon as I enter a folder - refunded.
Nice App. Support defined ports other than port 80. Other webdav apps only support port 80 which is usually blocked by ISP if webdav server is in home
